description: This book mainly consists of short stories done by the founders of Image Comics. The first story is by Rob Liefeld and is about his character Troll and his introduction into the Youngblood program. Next is a Stormwatch story by Jim Lee and Brandon Choi and a quick glimpse at Stormwatch Prime and their current status. Todd McFarlane does four pin ups showcasing characters he will be introducing into his Spawn series. Erik Larsen's story involves The Savage Dragon and the shows the risks of being involved with someone who is superpowered. Marc Silvestri show's the origin of Stryker from Cyberforce and Jim Valentino's Shadowhawk shows how he deals with criminals.
name: Prey

description:
1. "Final Secret of the Super-Sons" (Superman and Batman and computer generated Superman Jr and Batman Jr.) written by Denny O'Neil, penciled by Rich Buckler, inked by Dick Giordano, colored by Jerry Serpe and lettered by Ben Oda. Reprinted in Superman/Batman: Saga of the Super Sons.
  2. "Hell's Acre Savior!" (Green Arrow and Black Canary) written by Bob Haney, penciled by Trevor Von Eeden, inked by Armando Gil, colored by Jerry Serpe and lettered by Ben Oda.
  3. "Zeta-Death" (Adam Strange) written by Jack C. Harris, penciled by James Sherman, inked by Steve Mitchell, colored by Anthony Tollin and lettered by Mike Stevens. Story continues from Showcase #103.
  4. "Return to New Venice!" (Aquaman) written by Bob Rozakis, penciled by Jose Delbo, inked by Frank Chiaramonte, colored by Adrienne Roy and lettered by Gaspar.
  5. "The Graybeard Gang" (Captain Marvel Jr.) written by E. Nelson Bridwell, penciled by Don Newton, inked by Dave Hunt, colored by Adrienne Roy and lettered by Gaspar.

Notes:

  • Doctor Sivana cameo appearance in the Superman-Batman story.
  • Rope Arrow, Bola Arrow, Tear Gas Arrows and Stun Arrows used.
  • First appearance of the Aquaman Museum which is located in New Venice.
  • Aquaman story is a flashback origin story told through flashbacks, and the paintings and statues in the Aquaman Museum.
  • Atlanna, Tom Curry and Ocean Master cameo flashback appearances in the Aquaman story.
  • This issue contains the Hostess Superhero Ad, the Flash in "A Flash in the Dam".
name: Final Secret of the Super-Sons / Hell's Acre Savior! / Zeta-Death / Return to New Venice! / The Graybeard Gang

description: A classic creative team returns to deliver  DD action in a special double-sized issue that sets the stage for next month's Marvel Knights relaunch!  Matt Murdock is back in New York doing what he does best: protecting citizens as a defense lawyer and obtaining justice as the costumed vigilante known as Dardedevil!  When a cargo ship containing illegal weapons goes up in a ball of flames, The Man Without Fear must uncover the truth behind the mystery, while Matt must use all of his skills in the courtroom to protect the innocent man fingered as the key figure in the whole affair.  But to save a life, Daredevil will have to go through the combined might of Bullseye, Bushwacker and The Kingpin!  They brought you "Fall From Grace," now D.G. Chichester and Lee Weeks return to deliver this stand alone special issue.
name: Just One Good Story

description: Reprints Tales of Suspense #91, #81, #82.
name: The Uncanny Challenge of The Crusher!; The Return of The Titanium Man!; By Force of Arms!

description: This comic was published only in France and there is no English translated variant.

Concluding the four-issue stand-alone story-arc!  With all the players in place, Daredevil (who doesn't know he's DD) must stop the Kingpin's plan to distribute the device that rewired his brain!  Will Foggy Nelson be able to convince "Laurent" that he's really Matt Murdock, or will Mattstay on as an agent of S.H.I.E.L.D.?!
name: Flying Blind (Part 4)

description: Foggy and SHIELD begin to realize what has happened to Matt Murdock and exactly how much trouble he is in; Matt as Laurent finds himself facing off against Kingpin's goons.
name: Flying Blind (Part 3)

description: Undercover agent Laurent Levasseur does not know that in his real identity he is both blind lawyer Matt Murdock and the costumed adventurer known as Daredevil and wonders why he has a compulsion to roam the streets of France wearing tights and fighting bad guys; Foggy begins to look for the missing Matt; Kingpin sets his sights on Laurent.
name: Flying Blind (Part 2)

description:
FLYING BLIND PART 1

Daredevil is all alone in a foreign country. With no recollection of his life as Matt Murdock, the Man Without Fear has no support and no ties to his true identity. An existential crisis at its finest. Plus, who is Laurent Levasseur?
name: Flying Blind (Part 1)

description: Shaken by a failed and very nearly deadly romance, rookie Witchblade bearer Dani Baptiste confronts her feelings of betrayal and realizes this life, and the Witchblade, might not be for her. Dani seeks the advice of Sara Pezzini, who's had her share of experience with both the Witchblade and with being betrayed by men like Ian Nottingham and Kenneth Irons. It's time for some girl talk and some ass-kicking, with Dani's future as a bearer hanging in the balance!
name: Girls Night Out

description: The cosmic war has ended and, against all odds, the universe has survived. Now all that remains is to rebuild the cities and bury the dead, and Orion of the New Gods has taken it upon himself to aid in this massive effort. His first self-imposed mission: to deliver one particular casualty of the war home...to his enemies.
name: Tales of Times Past and Future

description: Giant robots and atomic monsters collide in a new miniseries by Warren Ellis and James Raiz (Transformers)! In the present day, Zoe Flynn, American pilot, is sent to Tokyo on an exchange scheme to pilot the ARCangels, immense combat robots used to protect Tokyo from the giant monsters that have been plaguing it for some 50 years!
name: Tokyo Storm Warning

description: Its the dawn of the new Millennium and John Constantine hosts a party.  The Vertigo Characters party like its 1999. We see The Swamp Thing, Doom Patrol, Black Orchid, Animal Man, Shade the Changing Man and John Constantine save the day when the world goes chaotic on New Years.  Will it be the End of the World Vertigo Style?
name: Totems

description: In the past Metahuman criminal Dr. Cobalt is apprehended by Hourman,and taken to prison following successfully hiding his locker. Meanwhile in the present day, Triumph foils several crimes alongside his team of operatives. He then attends a funeral where he glimpses Dr. Cobalt, running a search where it says Cobalt had died in prison six months beforehand due to cancer. Triumph however refuses to believe this opening a new case file as he fires Eddie from the team.
name: The Machine

description: Two women from Batman's life together at last! In the first of a two-part series, Batgirl and Catwoman join forces to thwart a murderer who preys on prostitutes...but what they uncover is a greater evil than either of them could hope to defeat alone!
name: Batgirl/Catwoman

description: The climactic follow-up to BIRDS OF PREY: CATWOMAN/BATGIRL! Nearly a decade after making an unlikely alliance, Catwoman and Batgirl are in very different places from where they started. Set in the present day, Catwoman is now a vigilante crusader for Gotham's neglected East End, while Batgirl has been paralyzed from the waist down by the Joker and fights crime as the all-seeing Oracle! When an old evil they thought vanquished returns to Gotham, they must set aside their differences once more. But this time their old foe is after them...and he's not the only one who's returned to the scene of the crime!
name: Catwoman/Oracle

description: In the final issue of Raven's solo adventure, the Medusa Mask grows more powerful. Can Raven save her schoolmates and herself as well?
name: Guilt
